Utterance: Hi there! It’s Ellie again. How have you been since our last session?
Hey, Ellie! I’ve been good, a bit busy with work and trying to find gigs.
That’s great to hear! Were you able to find any new opportunities?
Yes! I found an open mic night and performed last weekend.
Wow, that’s fantastic! How did it go?
It was nerve-wracking at first, but once I started singing, it felt amazing.
That’s wonderful! How did the audience respond?
They seemed to enjoy it! I got a few compliments afterward, which felt great.
That’s a huge accomplishment! How did it feel to receive that positive feedback?
It felt validating, like all the hard work was worth it.
That’s a beautiful feeling. Have you thought about how you can continue to build on that momentum?
I’m thinking of looking for more open mics and maybe even some small gigs.
That sounds like a solid plan! How can you hold yourself accountable to that goal?
I could set a specific number of events to attend each month.
That’s an excellent idea! How many do you think you could realistically aim for?
Maybe two or three a month?
That sounds achievable. Let’s set that as your goal for the next month. How about your meditation practice? Have you been able to incorporate it into your routine?
Yes! I’ve been meditating before bed, and it’s really helping me unwind.
I’m glad to hear that! How has it affected your sleep?
I’ve been sleeping better overall. I feel more relaxed when I go to bed.
That’s fantastic progress! Have you noticed any changes in your self-criticism since we last spoke?
I think I’m being kinder to myself. I still have moments, but I’m catching them quicker.
That’s great to hear! What techniques have been most helpful for you in shifting your mindset?
I’ve been practicing affirmations and reminding myself of my strengths.
Affirmations can be powerful! What’s one affirmation that resonates with you?
“I am a talented singer, and I deserve to share my voice.”
That’s a beautiful affirmation. How does saying that make you feel?
It gives me a boost of confidence and reminds me why I love singing.
That’s wonderful! How can you incorporate that affirmation into your daily routine?
I could say it every morning when I wake up.
That’s a great idea! Starting your day with positive affirmations can set a good tone. How about your relationships? How are things with your girlfriend?
They’re going really well. We’re supportive of each other’s goals.
That’s lovely to hear. Have you had any meaningful conversations about your dreams and aspirations?
Yes, we talk about our goals a lot. It feels good to have that support.
That’s so important. How do you feel when you share your dreams with her?
It feels freeing. She encourages me to go after what I want.
That’s a beautiful dynamic to have. Is there anything you’d like to work on in your relationship?
I think we could work on communication a bit more. Sometimes I hold back my feelings.
That’s a good insight. What do you think holds you back from expressing your feelings?
I worry about burdening her with my problems.
It’s understandable to feel that way, but sharing can strengthen your bond. How might you approach that?
Maybe I could pick a specific time to talk about my feelings when we’re both relaxed.

That sounds like a great plan! It’s important to create a safe space for those conversations. How about your family? Have you had any thoughts about your relationship with your brothers since we last talked?
I’ve been reflecting on it. I still don’t want to be around them, but I’m trying to let go of the anger.
That’s a healthy approach. How do you feel when you think about letting go of that anger?
It feels freeing, but it’s hard to fully let go.
It can be a process. What steps do you think you could take to work towards that?
I could write down my feelings about them and then find a way to release that energy.
That’s a good idea! Writing can be a powerful tool for processing emotions. Would you be open to trying that this week?
Yes, I’ll give it a shot.
Great! I’m looking forward to hearing how that goes. Is there anything else you’d like to discuss today?
No, I think we covered everything. Thank you for your support!
You’re very welcome! I’m proud of the progress you’ve made. I look forward to our next session.
Bye, Ellie!
Goodbye! Take care!
